top.value: This is a process fund used to support programme quality.
Transitory and chronically vulnerable rural people have access to a targeted, accountable and increasingly sustainable safety net

Ireland is working with UN agencies (under the leadership of UNAIDS) and will work with 4 local NGOs, to scale up coverage, utilization and access to quality SRH, HIV prevention, treatment, care and support services; while addressing socio-cultural and economic barriers hindering HIV preventive behaviours and constraint access to services. In addition, national and Karamoja region's capacity for planning, coodination, sustainable financing and information systems for tracking programmes will be strengthened.

Ireland will work with UNHCR and WFP to provide Humanitarian support to the refugees in Uganda. It will also work with WFP to support the School-feeding programme in Karamoja sub-region under the Humanitarian programme.
The aim of this budget line is to reduce the number of new HIV infections among youth and adults, in particular amongst adolescent girls
